main event: On 27 September 1956, a civilian reported sighting one white light, one blue-green light with a trailing tail, and a yellow glow. There was also a steady red light and a pulsating light in the area at the time of the sighting.
interesting points: The sighting included multiple unidentified flying objects with different characteristics, such as color and behavior.
The conclusion of the report suggested that the sighting could have been a possible balloon.
The report mentions the involvement of multiple military and civilian agencies in the investigation.
The details of the UFO sighting were documented in a typed text document from Project Blue Book, a government UFO investigation program.
The report includes specific timestamps, locations, and technical details about the sighting.
